  "definitions": [
    {
      "definition": "A primary cutaneous T-cell lymphoproliferative disorder composed of small to medium-sized CD4-positive, CD8-negative, and CD30-negative pleomorphic T-lymphocytes in the dermis. A small number of large pleomorphic T-lymphocytes, focal epidermotropism, and subcutaneous involvement may be seen. It usually presents with a solitary plaque or tumor on the face, neck, or upper trunk. The clinical behavior is almost always indolent, and most patients present with localized disease.",
      "type": "DEFINITION",
      "source": "NCI"
    }
  ],
